library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(countrycode)
suppressMessages(library(ggmap))
library(leaflet)
TB<-read.csv("tallestbuildings.csv")
TB=TB%>%separate(City, c("City","Country"), sep = "\xff")
TB$Country<-countrycode(gsub("\\(|\\)","",TB$Country),"iso2c","country.name")
TB=rename(TB, HeightFeet=Height..ft.)
TB$HeightFeet <- as.numeric(gsub(",","",TB$HeightFeet))
TB$Height..m.<-NULL
TB$CityCountry <- paste(TB$City,TB$Country)
nBuildings<-data.frame(TB %>% 
    count(City))
latlon<-geocode(as.character(nBuildings$City),output = c("latlon"))

nBuildings$lat<-latlon$lat
nBuildings$lon<-latlon$lon
map=get_map(location="Italy",maptype="roadmap",source="google",zoom=1)
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=Italy&zoom=1&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=roadmap&language=en-EN
## Source : https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address=Italy
TBmap=ggmap(map)
TBmap=TBmap+geom_point(data=nBuildings,
            aes(lon,lat,color=City),size=nBuildings$n,alpha = 0.5)+theme(panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
                 panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
                axis.text = element_blank(),axis.title = element_blank(),
                axis.ticks = element_blank())+ labs(title = "Cities with the Tallest Buildings")
print(TBmap)
## Warning: Removed 1 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

leaflet() %>% addTiles()%>%addCircleMarkers(data=nBuildings,popup=~n,color=~City,radius=~n*5)
## Assuming 'lon' and 'lat' are longitude and latitude, respectively
